@startuml activity-content-strategy
'' PlantUML over Mermaid because the content-view Strategy is an ORDERED cond (first matching arm wins),
'' so a top-to-bottom decision cascade with dashed «planned» future branches is the right shape; PlantUML
'' activity if/elseif preserves the precedence order and lets planned arms be drawn dashed/grey.
'' Literal palette hexes: teal #2D9574 renderer outputs, green #67B11D markdown, red #E0211D error,
'' grey #DDDDDD «planned».
!include _vv-theme.iuml

title content-view Strategy — selecting the document body by precedence (first match wins)\n(vinary.ui.views/content-view)

start
:render content-view\n(doc = @[:doc/active], tabs = @[:tabs]);

if (tabs empty?) then (yes)
  #2D9574:[watermark]\n.vv-watermark / .vv-shield;
  stop
else (no)
endif

if (:doc/error present?) then (yes)
  #E0211D:[:div.vv-error "Error: …"];
  stop
else (no)
endif

if (:doc/kind = "image"?) then (yes)
  #2D9574:[:div.vv-image-view\n[:img {:src "file://"+path}]];
  stop
else (no)
endif

if (:doc/html present?) then (yes)
  #67B11D:[markdown-body html]\n(form-3; set! innerHTML);
  stop
else (no — render in flight)
  #DDDDDD:[:div.vv-empty "Rendering…"];
  stop
endif

'' ----- Forthcoming branches (planned): drawn detached + dashed/grey -----
partition "Forthcoming (planned) registry arms" #line.dashed;line:999999 {
  #DDDDDD:«planned» kind = "pdf"\n→ native BrowserView;
  #DDDDDD:«planned» kind = "diagram"\n→ d2/PlantUML/Mermaid → SVG;
  #DDDDDD:«planned» kind = "source"\n→ tree-sitter view;
  note right #EEEEEE
    Today the Strategy is a fixed cond; the planned
    "registry as data" replaces these arms with a
    {kind → render-fn} table (open for extension,
    closed for modification).
  end note
  detach
}

legend right
  |= Colour |= Branch / concept |
  |<#2D9574>| renderer view output (watermark, image) |
  |<#67B11D>| Markdown body (rendered :doc/html) |
  |<#E0211D>| error view (:doc/error) |
  |<#DDDDDD>| "Rendering…" placeholder + «planned» future arms |
  Arms are tried top-to-bottom; the FIRST matching condition wins.
endlegend
@enduml
